								</blockquote>
								On October 18, 2009, Pithruvedi had its formal inauguration from His Beatitude Cardinal
								Mar George Alencherry, the present Major Archbishop of the Syro-Malabar Catholic Church,
								at the Presentation Convent School Ground in Nerul. In this first assembly, H.E. Mar
								Thomas Elavanal promulgated the Pithruvedi By-Laws.
								<br><br>
								The primary objective of this association is to bring the members of the parish
								community together in their shared religious beliefs by nurturing them with spiritual
								principles and teachings. Pithruvedi endeavors to instill the significance of
								selflessness, prioritizing family values, and leading the family in a life centered
								around prayer and worship.
								<br><br>
								The members of Pithruvedi solely host the feast of St. Joseph, the patron saint of the
								parish, which includes liturgy, choir, and Ottunercha, in addition to actively
								participating and carrying out each of their respective tasks throughout every parish
